purpose: The commit fixes an issue where queuing commands may cause a User Authentication Failure (UAF) when HCI_UNREGISTER is set for the Bluetooth device.

The commit removes an unnecessary include of 'asm/termios.h' in 'n_hdlc.c', as it is already included by 'linux/tty.h'. The author argues that this simplifies the codebase and improves its organization.
The commit updates documentation for a store metric 'N/A', reflecting changes in the report table.

The commit addresses issues related to vma lock handling during split vma and range unmapping in the hugetlb subsystem of the Linux kernel. It fixes race conditions and prevents double freeing of structures, improves the sharing code, and updates open vm_ops.
The commit adds AVDD and MICVDD supplies to the realtek,rt5682s codec in the ASoC (Audio Subsystem) by documenting them in the binding. This is done to be used by other drivers.
The commit fixes a resource leak in the zorro7xx_remove_one() function by adding an iounmap() call.
The commit removes an unused work field from struct mlx5e_async_ctx.

The commit modifies the 'cfg80211_auth_request::key_idx' member of a struct to be signed, in order to avoid warnings from static checkers such as smatch when the key is NULL. This change ensures that the key_idx can only take values within the range -1..3.
The commit sorts CONFIG_SURFACE_PLATFORMS in a way that matches savedefconfig's sorting method, which should have no functional change.
The commit introduces a new function mcp251xfd_is_fd_mode() and replaces an open coded check with this function to determine if the chip's FIFOs are configured for CAN-FD mode.
The commit skips self-tests when RTC is not present to avoid failing them.
The commit removes a redundant assignment to a variable in the ALSA: echoaudio module, addressing a Clang scan build warning.
The commit allows rcuscale to function without RCU Tasks, reducing kernel size and complexity of certain tracing operations.
The commit removes duplicate lines in a header file 'spte.h' related to KVM x86 MMU.
The commit reverts a change to prevent a no read situation caused by using dcfclk based clk table when dcfclk states are disabled.
The commit adds a compatible string for the Renesas RZ/V2L SoC's Bifrost Mali-G31 GPU.
The commit renames a struct 'pcie_port' to 'dw_pcie_rp' in the DW PCIe core driver entities for consistency with other names.
The commit addresses a Clang warning related to format specification in a C file of the AMD xGBE network driver. It explains the issue, provides relevant documentation links, and suggests a solution.

The commit modifies the MIPS jump_label function to fix a compatibility branch range check issue by casting the upper bound of the branch range to long for signed comparison, preventing a warning triggered by negative offset.
The commit removes a case from SetHwReg8188EU() function and calls a function directly instead. This is part of an ongoing effort to eliminate the unwanted hal layer.
The commit aims to address sparse warnings introduced while adding errata by declaring non-global symbols as static in arm64 architecture.
The commit removes incorrect interrupt flags on MDSS nodes to fix an issue related to the MDSS interrupt provider.
The commit modifies the 'v4l2-ctrls' module to allocate arrays in 'ctrl_ref' structure, preparing it for changing the array size from a driver.
The commit adds support for new PMICs and SoCs to the socinfo driver.
The commit aims to modify the wifi driver rtl8xxxu to recognize all possible chip cuts (versions) instead of printing 'unknown' for versions greater than E.
The commit removes a custom software enable count from PRCMU clocks in the ux500 core, as it is already maintained by the core's software enable count.
The commit aims to remove unnecessary #ifdef CONFIG_XIP_KERNEL usage in the codebase by grouping together similar cases and moving the pt_ops macro adjacent to it.
The commit enables QUP and GPI DMA hardware to add functioning I2C nodes later.
This commit fixes comments for better readability and consistency, corrects a typo, and adheres to coding style guidelines.

The commit aims to fix an infinite loop issue in the 'release_swfw_sync' function, which may occur due to a failure to acquire the hardware semaphore. If the hardware is surprise-removed, the function will log an error and quit.
The commit updates the pcm31668a driver to use modern terminology for clocking, as part of a move to remove old style defines for bus clocks.
The commit removes a pointless piece of code that is no longer needed as IS_SWAPFILE is always defined.
The commit adds support for GTP echo response, addressing a situation where there is no userspace daemon to handle GTP messages, and ensuring compliance with the GTP specification.

The commit replaces cpumask_next_* with cpumask_first_* where appropriate to make it more effective, and creates a new function cpumask_first_zero(). The author is Yury Norov and the change has been tested by Wolfram Sang.

The commit removes a call to 'dtim_assoc' IOVAR from the brcmfmac driver, addressing an issue where this call always fails during STA roaming, causing a console message. The changes ensure that the host driver will no longer try to get TIM information from firmware.
The commit adds support for a platform without amplifier for the alc5682 headset codec by connecting it to SSP0 following Intel BT offload design.
The commit modifies the io_uring/net to fail zerocopy sendmsg when unsupported by socket.
The commit aims to improve the loading of a specific package (xeCJK) in certain Linux distributions by testing its existence before loading it, which should prevent errors related to its absence.
The commit modifies a macro definition in a header file to allow for 'case' macros without parentheses, addressing errors reported by checkpatch.pl tool.
The commit converts simple-KMS helpers to atomic helpers for easier code sharing among drivers, with no functional changes.
The commit adds a jpeg decoding worker interface to ensure that three HWs run in parallel in MT8195.
The commit removes unnecessary VPRINTK() calls and ata_scsi_dump_cdb() function from the libata library, as this information can be retrieved from other sources like tracepoints or scsi tracing.

The commit adds support for zstate during extended vblank in the drm/amd/display module when entering FREESYNC_STATE_VIDEO. It calculates the time gained from extra vblank lines and allows zstate entry if the time gained is greater than 5 ms. An optimized value for min_dst_y_next_start is calculated and written to its register. Default values are restored when exiting freesync.
The commit fixes a Control Flow Integrity (CFI) violation in the hqd_destroy() callback function by updating its function pointer prototype to match the actual type of the third parameter.
The commit corrects a typo in the 'resets' property name for pinctrl bindings in the stm32 driver.
The commit modifies the GCC 12 warning for an array bounds issue in the 'ath9k_hw_resettxqueue' function of the 'mac.c' file in the wireless driver for ath9k.
The commit changes the function used for resuming a power management runtime from pm_runtime_get_sync to pm_runtime_resume_and_get. The change is intended to simplify the code.
The commit moves the io_uring related fixed file installation and removal code to the filetable code where it belongs. It also changes the helpers to take a ctx rather than an io_kiocb.
The commit separates G1 and G2 nodes for independent decoder blocks in the vpu-blk-ctrl power-domain controller, updating device tree bindings to support separate nodes.
The commit removes a macro named IWL_DEVICE_BZ_COMMON from the codebase.
